# Yankees Regression Analysis (STA145 Replication Package)

This project explores the relationship between home runs and hits among New York Yankees players using linear regression. It includes data import, cleaning, analysis, and visualization steps, aligned with STA145 course expectations.

## Contents
- `data/`: Cleaned dataset of Yankees players (2000â€“2025)
- `scripts/`: R script for regression and diagnostics
- `figures/`: Scatterplot, residual plot, histogram
- `tables/`: Descriptive stats, regression output, assumption checks
- `report/`: Full write-up with rubric alignment

## How to Run
1. Clone the repo
2. Open `scripts/analysis.R` in RStudio
3. Run the script to generate figures and model output
4. View results in `figures/` and `tables/`
5. See `report/yankees_regression_report.docx` for full interpretation

